OL,5, The Food and Drug Administration (FDA) 
OL,6, has announced it will be changing a    
OL,7, current three month abstinence policy  
OL,8, for blood donations from gay men.      
OL,10,FCurrent rules only allow donations if a
OL,11,Fman has not had sex with another man   
OL,12,Ffor that period.                       
OL,14,FUnder new "individual risk-based" draft
OL,15,Frules, all potential donors would be   
OL,16,Fasked about new or multiple sexual     
OL,17,Fpartners in the past three months.     
OL,19,FThe FDA hopes this change will         
OL,20,Fencourage more blood donations.        
